%% Team271-Lib — Periodic Loop Data Flow (one robot cycle)
%% Shows how the library sequences each TimedRobot cycle and where the
%% desired-to-actual state reconciliation happens.
%% Source of truth: ADR-007 (centralized CAN refresh), ADR-010 (forEachSafe
%%                  exception isolation), ADR-014 (desired-to-actual pattern)

sequenceDiagram
    participant TRobot
    participant HWMgr as HardwareManager
    participant CTREMgr as CTREManager
    participant SubMgr as SubsystemManager
    participant Sub as Subsystem
    participant NT as Telemetry

    Note over TRobot: one periodic cycle begins
    TRobot->>HWMgr: refreshAll
    HWMgr->>CTREMgr: refreshAll
    CTREMgr-->>HWMgr: one bulk CAN read
    Note right of CTREMgr: consistent timestamps per ADR-007

    TRobot->>SubMgr: forEachSafe robotPeriodicBefore
    loop each subsystem
        SubMgr->>Sub: robotPeriodicBefore
        Note right of Sub: read sensors and update ACTUAL state (ADR-014)
    end

    Note over TRobot: operator input or scheduled AutoMove updates DESIRED state
    TRobot->>SubMgr: forEachSafe robotPeriodicAfter
    loop each subsystem
        SubMgr->>Sub: robotPeriodicAfter
        Note right of Sub: reconcile DESIRED vs ACTUAL and command motors with timeouts (ADR-011, ADR-014)
    end

    TRobot->>SubMgr: forEachSafe outputTelemetry
    loop each subsystem
        SubMgr->>Sub: outputTelemetry
        Sub->>NT: publish outputs
    end
    Note right of SubMgr: forEachSafe catches exceptions and throttles Elastic alerts (ADR-010)
